T1  - Cultural Conflict and Merger Failure: An Experimental Approach
AU  - Weber, Roberto A.
AU  - Camerer, Colin F.
Y1  - 2003/04/01
PY  - 2003
DA  - 2003/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.49.4.400.14430
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.49.4.400.14430
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 400
EP  - 415
VL  - 49
IS  - 4
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - We use laboratory experiments to explore merger failure due to conflicting organizational cultures. We introduce a laboratory paradigm for studying organizational culture that captures several key elements of the phenomenon. In our experiments, we allow subjects in ?firms? to develop a culture, and then merge two firms. As expected, performance decreases following the merging of two laboratory firms. In addition, subjects overestimate the performance of the merged firm and attribute the decrease in performance to members of the other firm rather than to situational difficulties created by conflicting culture.
AB  - We use laboratory experiments to explore merger failure due to conflicting organizational cultures. We introduce a laboratory paradigm for studying organizational culture that captures several key elements of the phenomenon. In our experiments, we allow subjects in ?firms? to develop a culture, and then merge two firms. As expected, performance decreases following the merging of two laboratory firms. In addition, subjects overestimate the performance of the merged firm and attribute the decrease in performance to members of the other firm rather than to situational difficulties created by conflicting culture.
